Set the font size used when rendering text.

### syntax

~~~ python
textSize(size)
~~~

### parameters

size | font size

### examples

#### setting the font size


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "text-size", "setting-the-font-size.png" %>


~~~ python
def init():
   textFont('data/fonts/DroidSans.ttf')

def display():
   size = 12

   textSize(size)
   text('font-size={}'.format(size), 0, 0, 5)
   size += 2
   
   textSize(size)
   text('font-size={}'.format(size), 0, 0, 3)
   size += 2
   
   textSize(size)
   text('font-size={}'.format(size), 0, 0, 0)
   size += 2
   
   textSize(size)
   text('font-size={}'.format(size), 0, 0, -3)
   size += 2
   
   textSize(size)
   text('font-size={}'.format(size), 0, 0, -5)
   size += 2
~~~
